    "content": "<p>$$ \\text { Consider the following closed loop control system } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh25i49t/3215e852-5b1d-4d60-a9fc-0ae98607e417/2bd97910-af5c-11f0-8ff7-4f6304b9a291/file-jaoe38c1mh25i49u.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh25i49t/3215e852-5b1d-4d60-a9fc-0ae98607e417/2bd97910-af5c-11f0-8ff7-4f6304b9a291/file-jaoe38c1mh25i49u.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2020 Control Systems - Basic of Control Systems Question 1 English\"></p>\n<p>where $G(s)=\\frac{1}{s(s+1)}$ and $C(s)=K \\frac{s+1}{s+3}$. If the steady state error for a unit ramp input is 0.1 , then the value of $K$ is $\\_\\_\\_\\_$ .</p>",
    "options": [],
    "correct_options": [],
    "answer": "<p>30</p>",
    "explanation": "<p>$$ \\text { Given : Consider the following closed loop control system, } $$</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mh25i3ol/39fa2e2a-cd6e-4feb-9cae-19e93beb7220/2b64e550-af5c-11f0-8ff7-4f6304b9a291/file-jaoe38c1mh25i3om.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mh25i3ol/39fa2e2a-cd6e-4feb-9cae-19e93beb7220/2b64e550-af5c-11f0-8ff7-4f6304b9a291/file-jaoe38c1mh25i3om.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"GATE ECE 2020 Control Systems - Basic of Control Systems Question 1 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}Where,\\,\\, &amp; G(s)=\\frac{1}{s(s+1)} \\\\ &amp; C(s)=\\frac{K(s+1)}{(s+3)} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Open loop transfer function is given by,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} \\mathrm{OLTF} &amp; =G(s) C(s) \\\\ G^{\\prime}(s) &amp; =\\frac{1}{s(s+1)} \\frac{K(s+1)}{(s+3)}=\\frac{K}{s(s+3)} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Given : For ramp input, $e_{s s}=0.1$</p>\n<p>$e_{s s}$ for unit ramp input $=\\frac{1}{K_v}$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}Where,\\,\\,\\ &amp; K_v=\\text { Velocity error constant } \\\\ &amp; K_v=\\lim _{s \\rightarrow 0} s[\\mathrm{OLTF}] \\\\ &amp; K_v=\\lim _{s \\rightarrow 0} s G^{\\prime}(s)=\\lim _{s \\rightarrow 0} s \\frac{K}{s(s+3)}=\\frac{K}{3} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Steady state error is given by,</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned} &amp; e_{s s}=\\frac{1}{K_v} \\\\ &amp; e_{s s}=\\frac{1}{K / 3}=\\frac{3}{K} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}So,\\,\\, &amp; \\frac{3}{K}=0.1 \\\\ &amp; K=30 \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>Hence, the value of $K$ is $\\mathbf{3 0}$.</p>",
